title: Stump - 4th Peel Session
description:
Stump&#039;s 4th Peel session, captured from radio broadcast. Recorded 1988-08-14, first broadcast 1988-09-13. 

Kev Hopper - bass
Chris Salmon - guitars
Rob McKahey - drums
Mick Lynch - vox

01 The Song&#039;s Remains
02 Thelma
03 Strayte &#039;n&#039; Narrow
04 Seven Sisters

Sound quality isn&#039;t wonderful, coming from 2nd generation tape. There&#039;s a wee bit of hiss and John Peel can be heard over the music in a couple of places. The edits are a bit ropey, too and there&#039;s even some fluctuation of recording level at the beginning of "Strayte &#039;n&#039; Narrow" but, hey, it&#039;s very listenable and I&#039;ve never seen it elsewhere, so if you feel like moaning, don&#039;t. Just give us a better version instead.

Stump&#039;s 2nd Peel session is here: http://thepiratebay.se/tor/4253430  
Stump&#039;s 3rd Peel session is here: http://thepiratebay.se/tor/4253439
